# UIStatusSystem  (sbx)

## Purpose
Keeps the UI status text in sync with the spawn count. Returns early until both
SpawnerSingletonComponent and SandboxConfigSingletonComponent are present; lazily creates
StatusDisplaySingletonComponent on the first ready frame. When the spawn count differs from the last
value shown, it finds the status text element by UUID and emits a UIUpdateTextOneFrameComponent with
the new "Spawned: N" string.

## Input Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| SpawnerSingletonComponent | read | Current spawn count; guard |
| SandboxConfigSingletonComponent | read | Status text element id and font id; guard |
| BaseComponent | read | Locates the status text element by UUID |
| StatusDisplaySingletonComponent | write | Last-shown spawn count (change detection) |

## Output Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| StatusDisplaySingletonComponent | write / add (deferred) | Created once; updated when the count changes |
| UIUpdateTextOneFrameComponent | add (oneframe) | Emitted on the status text element when the count changes |
